And out of this rare combination of practical wisdom and poetical sentiment there grows that noblest part of his moral teaching wh1ch is distinct from schools and sects, and touches at times upon chords more spiritual than those who do not look below the surface would readily detect. Hence, in spite of his occasional sins, he has always found indulgent favour with the clergy of every Church.
